Sodic Heads for Biggest Gain in 3 Months After Declaring Sales

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-10-16T11:49:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/sodic-heads-for-biggest-gain-in-3-months-after-declaring-sales.html
Six of October Development &
Investment (OCDI)  Co., an Egyptian luxury property developer, headed
for the biggest daily gain in more than three months after
announcing sales for the first nine-months of the year.  Shares of the Cairo-based company also known as Sodic
jumped 6 percent to 13.9 Egyptian pounds at 1:21 p.m. in Cairo,
poised for the biggest daily gain since July 13. The benchmark
EGX 30 Index advanced 1.5 percent.  Sales reached 570 million Egyptian pounds ($95.5 million)
in the first nine-months of the year, Sodic said in a filing to
the Egyptian bourse today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  